cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata in this
  file. A DOI for tagged releases is reserved on Zenodo (auto-minted on
  the first GitHub release).
title: "ECAA-workflow"
abstract: >-
  Deterministic, offline compiler that turns a natural-language
  bioinformatics project description into a self-contained,
  agent-executable RO-Crate package. Wraps the compiler with a
  full-lifecycle conversational shell (closed LLM tool vocabulary,
  deterministic state machine) so domain scientists drive intake,
  blocker resolution, result review, rerun/amendment, and session
  branching entirely through chat. Conformance is enforced by an
  embedded ECAA validator over claims, evidence, and decision substrate.
type: software
license: Apache-2.0
